				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 64~HAve Charm Now What?<a name="17399"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 27 04 11:24 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi there!
<br />

<br />
I find swarm charm kiting in PoN to be much less boring and way more lucrative than kiting HoH mobs running in circles for 5-7 minutes till they are dead. I social agro the 9 Hoggoblins you can pull without agroing Nameds summoners, taking a beating while doing so, if you are going to do it for the first time I suggest getting a virtue, just in case... and try not to get in the water when going down hill Seloed and all, my swimming doesn't suck but still... Then I make them follow me to a safe corner between hedge and the tabletop with the horsies (Gloom Nighmares), so if noobs train crocs, uglies or other kind of sumoner/caster menace, you might avoid the agro.
<br />

<br />
Then I charm one, send it against another and circle around the 2 mobs for the rest to agro the charmed mob, while doing so I hit F1 twice so if charm breaks I quickly recharm the same mob so no loose ends. In about 3/5 secs, charmed pet HPs drop to 40% (with the other 8 Gobbies beating on pet), I sing invisibility to break charm and chant mob dead... usually 10% or less HPs when it breaks. Wash, Rinse, Repeat. When less mobs, I sing invisibility a bit later so ex-pet close to 10% HPs left when I break charm. 
<br />

<br />
I find 3 Gobbies give the same experience as a HoH mob, maybe a bit more. In any case, the first 3 mobs die pretty quick. In about 3 minutes. The remaining 6 die in another 7 minutes or so. So, experience has to be pretty much the same, if not better, and they drop diamonds, and EPs that I give away for free every 2 weeks or so at PoK.
<br />

<br />
The only drawback is, you run out of Gobbies, but the 1st one dies so fast that I usually go back at Gobbies camp and pull it (if up) for some Wraith smacking at Gobbies-Camp Group Spot. Notice that, while snareable, Wraiths are way faster than Gobbies so Gobbie pet doesn't catch up and I end up charming Wraith (which has higher Magic Resistance - thus charms are usually shorter). I don't have snare/slow up cause I only have one slot free and I use it for regular slow since Gobbies are snare inmune. Helps when 2 Gobbies left and one has 80% HPs and the other one has 30% HPs. I charm the low HPs one and slow the 80% HPs one before sending pet, then chant mob to bits...
<br />

<br />
I do PoN kiting while LFGing... I get 4 blues and a half of AA exp (9 Gobbies - about half a blue each).
<br />

<br />
My 2 cp...
<br />

<br />
Nilufer</span></td>
