			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 64~HAve Charm Now What?<a name="17565"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 28 04 2:48 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I love PoN as well and the gobs are great fun. 
<br />

<br />
Mephits are another choice, but are a bit more difficult. 
<br />
You will need to get up on the ledge where the Gloom Nightmares reside first. 
<br />
Many bards choose the &quot;run like h*ll and fade&quot; method through the caves. I prefer to use the &quot;charm, attack and get summoned&quot; method. I find a Vexed Banshee and charm her, send it after one of the Nightmares on the ledge and just wait for charm to break. She will summon you to the top of the ledge. Once there, you can fade or recharm her and have the Nightmare finish her off. You don't want to waste any time getting rid of the summoning banshee since you now have a horse that can hit for 500+ to deal with. I usually run tight circles and chant the horse down. 
<br />

<br />
When the first horse is dead, you need to kill the one next to the cave because, no matter what, he will eventually agro while you're kiting the Mephits. You can chant him down or charm a Mephit. 
<br />
Keep Requiem of Time on the Nightmare and a Mephit pet can win.
<br />

<br />
There are 3 different kinds of Mephits: Mephits, Misery Mephits and Agony Mephits. 
<br />

<br />
Mephits are the only ones that are charmable. They don't cast and can be snared and mezzed. 
<br />

<br />
Misery Mephits are casters, wizards to be exact that will try to nuke and root you. Always have resists up when dealing with them. They cannot be lulled but can be mezzed. I will keep mez up just in case he manages to land a root. All the Mephits hit for 383 so yes, root is bad.
<br />

<br />
Agony Mephits are the enchanters. They are rare, but can drop spectrals and a nice earring you can sell. Keep resists up as well. I've had an Agony charm me before and than up and leave. Quite annoying.
<br />
Keep in mind that Misery and Agony Mephits will gate and regen fast so that's another good reason to keep mez up.
<br />

<br />
Mephit caves are profitable as well. The blood sells pretty good and you can get gems and vendor loot as well.
<br />

<br />
<i>Kyarah</i>
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
