				<td colspan="2"><span>Yep, as long as charm holds long enough for her to get enough damage she will summon you. Just keep her targeted all the time in case it breaks too soon and when you finally reach the top so you can recharm her fast. 
<br />
Also in all the chaos, make sure you don't run into the Shade while your kiting the horse. His agro isn't too wide but sometimes you can get spun around and forget which way your going. 
<br />

<br />
There are usually enough charmables around. You may have to keep Veeshan up and run past a Misery to get to a regular every now and than. I've had a few times in which I had to run past 2 Miserys to pull a regular. I kept Veeshan up, and dotted one of the Miserys to keep him chasing me while I used the pet to kill the other. I had a few times in which they gated but that was just more annoying than anything since the Misery don't summon.
<br />
I also noticed that once you clear a little of the cave out and pull several at a time, the Miserys from way in the back don't follow along. I still don't know why.
<br />

<br />
And one little note, I can't remember but I believe the Agony Mephits do summon. Been a long time since I saw one.
<br />

